{
  "id": "indus_phase32_t4_sa_m77_tb_lm",
  "name": "Indus Phase-32 T4 \u2014 SA Decipherment M77 \u2192 Dravidian Tamil LM (P30-H1)",
  "description": "Phase-32 T4 v2: SA decipherment M77 \u2192 Dravidian Syllable LM. Uses dravidian_syllable_lm.json (2293 syllable bigrams from DEDR roots + clean TB aksharas, 5\u00d7 richer than word-level LM). Syllable-level matching is more appropriate for short Indus inscriptions (mean 3.2 signs). Original word-level run was NEUTRAL (LM too sparse). This syllable-level variant provides stronger discriminative power. Citations: E.1 (DEDR), A.12 (Mahadevan 2003 TB)., with HIGH/MEDIUM INDUS_FINAL_ANCHORS as fixed starting points (333 entries). This test is non-circular: the LM is built from independent Tamil lexical/literary sources (DEDR, Sangam corpus), NOT from the Indus corpus itself. If SA finds a mapping significantly above a random null baseline, it is the strongest positive evidence for the Dravidian hypothesis produced so far. Null result = strong structural evidence against. Cites: A.1 (Mahadevan 1977), E.1 (DEDR/Burrow+Emeneau), E.3 (Sangam), C.2 (Parpola 2010).",
